Subject: [PATCH 4/8] feat(pronunciation): custom recorder with auto-stop VAD +
 explicit submit

Replace the vue-audio-recorder widget in PronunciationQuestion.vue with a
purpose-built recorder:
- getUserMedia + ScriptProcessor capturing PCM and mic energy in one graph
- energy-based VAD auto-stops ~1.2s after the student stops speaking
  (manual Stop still available); guards min/max duration
- native <audio> playback + an explicit "Submit for scoring" button,
  replacing the widget's hidden disk/save icon
- rejects empty/silent takes before submitting
- encodes mp3 client-side via lamejs (satisfies ADAPT's audio/mpeg-only
  upload check); uploads via axios, then the existing /score + gradeback flow
- tight, self-owned layout (no CSS overrides against a third-party widget)

Add lamejs as a direct dependency (previously only transitive via
vue-audio-recorder).

